{\fs24\insrsid3496465\charrsid11357524 separate}{\fs24\insrsid9261759  help option}{\fs24\insrsid3496465\charrsid11357524 .}{\fs24\insrsid3496465 
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 (}{\fs24\insrsid9261759 6}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 ) }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Assembler output}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid3496465 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Assembler output (in binary or hex) is shown in this area against the memory locations at which the output is loaded. Two checkboxes are provided to select between binary and hex output formats. }{
\fs24\insrsid9261759 
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Since the assembler is one-pass, it uses a technique known as 'back-patching' to fill in memory addresses of labels which are defined after use. Information about }{\fs24\insrsid9261759 any }{
\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 such 'back-patched' labels is listed separately after the assembly output.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid3496465 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 (}{\fs24\insrsid9261759 7}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 ) }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 I/O ports}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid3496465 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 The simulator provides 24 I/O ports, with addresses from decimal 0 to 23 (i.e. 00 to 17 hex). This area of the screen shows contents of these I/O ports in 8-bit binary. 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid3496465 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 On an IN (input) operation, the simulator prompts the user for 8-bit binary input. The input supplied is 'read in' and also displayed at the appropriate location in this area.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid3496465 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 On an OUT (output) operation, the simulator displays the output byte at the appropriate location in this area.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid3496465 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Program references to higher numbered port numbers treated as 'no operations'.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid3496465 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 (}{\fs24\insrsid9261759 8}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 ) }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Messages to user}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid3496465 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 In this area, relevant error and other informative messages from the simulator, assembler and the running program are displayed for the user's benefit.
