\par }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 B. MENU OPTIONS}{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515 
\par }{\fs24\ul\insrsid7371373\charrsid11357524 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Note: Depending on the simulator operation in progress, some of the menu options are disabled. For example, if there is no program in the code area, then the Assemble and Go menu options are disabled.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 (1) }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 File menu}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 File menu offers the options 'New', 'Open', 'Import', 'Close', 'Save', 'Save As' and 'Exit'. These options have the usual meaning as in most other GUI application programs.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 (2) }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Edit menu}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524  
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Edit menu offers options 'Undo', 'Redo', 'Cut', 'Copy' and 'Paste', which have the same meaning as in any other editor program.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 (3) }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Run menu}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524  
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Run menu offers options 'Assemble', 'Step', 'Go', 'Pause', 'Reset' and 'Resume'. Since these options are specific to the simulator, they are explained in brief below:
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 a. }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Assemble}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524  - Causes program in the code area to be assembled. Assembly errors, if any, are displayed in the message area.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 b. }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Step}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524  - 'Single step of execution', i.e. causes the single instruction pointed to by PC to be executed. 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 c. }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Go}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 
 - Causes the program to be executed (i.e. run) from the current PC value. Execution proceeds until one of the following events occurs:}{\fs24\insrsid10094515 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid9261759\charrsid11357524 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 - a HALT instruction is executed, 
\par - a breakpoint is encountered, or
\par - the 'pause' option is selected to pause the running program.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 d. }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Reset}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 
 - Resets the state of the simulator, i.e. registers, flags, I/O ports and PC are set to zeros. Message area of the screen is cleared. Note that memory contents are not reset - i.e. the program which is loaded into memory continues to reside there.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 e. }{\fs24\ul\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 Resume}{\fs24\insrsid10094515\charrsid11357524 
 - Execution resumes from specified PC value. The option is similar to 'Go', but the user is prompted for a value of PC from which to resume execution. If null value is supplied by the user, 
execution resumes from current value of PC (i.e. then this option has the same effect as 'Go').
\par }{\fs24\insrsid7371373 
